Columbia has the third most efficient endowment in the long-run.

The average measure of efficiency (Sharpe Ratio) among top institutions is 0.781. Long-term efficiency is based on 10 Year Return Marginal Propensity to Invest risk estimates.

The Sharpe ratio measures risk-adjusted performance

of an investment. It is calculated by dividing an

endowment’s excess returns by its volatility.
